    <p class="articlelabel"> Great Minds Open Doors to Great Futures </p>

    <p class="date"> June 5, 2017 <span class="org"> Great Minds STEM Society</span></p>


        <div class="articletext">

        <p>Dear Participants: <br> <br> Welcome. I created Great Minds STEM Society for students who are unable to reach their full academic potential due to lack of educational opportunities. Great Minds does focus on STEM subjects, but we are not going to ignore your other academic and personal needs. As someone who was born and raised in South Los Angeles, I know your struggle, I know your needs, I founded this organization with all of you in mind. I simply want to limit whatever struggle you are facing academically by giving you something I never had which is a mentor, someone who will guide you through every step of the way and genuinely cares about where you are headed in life. All of us are capable of being so much more than we realize, it’s just that sometimes we need a guide or an influential person who can identify our potential. I am here to lead you to a greater path one without judgement and ridicule. This organization is for you to learn freely whether you want to listen your favorite genre of music while conducting experiments or feel that need to dance, play games, or take multiple breaks. Your method of learning is ultimately up to you, all I ask is that you get the job done.
 </p>

        <p>Great Minds STEM Society is a family environment, if someone needs help we lend our hands out to support them in any capacity we can, all participants will be held to that same standard of helping their peers. Our focus is to be better as a whole, if one person fails we all fail, but if we work together towards the same goal I promise you we will all succeed. I believe that you and I can achieve great things together, you are as important to me as I am to you.
        </p>

        <p>I look forward to forming genuine relationships with all of you. I feel that this is something truly special in the making and I hope you feel the same. Great Minds STEM Society was established for great people like you.
        </p>

        <p>Sincerely, <br><br> Brian Everitt <br> Founder</p>
