    <p class="articlelabel"> Great Minds Open Doors to Great Futures </p>

    <p class="date"> June 5, 2017 <span class="org"> Great Minds STEM Society</span></p>

        <div class="articletext">

        <p>Dear Parents: <br> <br> Welcome. We look forward to working with you and your children, as you are a vital part of their success. Ongoing research shows that family engagement improves students’ educational achievement. Students with engaged families earn higher grades and test scores, have increased social skills, and improved behavior. Setting goals with your children and fostering achievement of those goals is an important way to increase your involvement. While we will be committed to the academic success of your children, it is extremely important that you reinforce the importance of their education and encourage them to be better students. Most importantly, hold them accountable when they are not satisfactorily meeting academic benchmarks set forth by you and/or their school.</p>

        <p>As the founder of this organization, I will ensure that your child has every opportunity for success. They will be presented with new, innovative material and at times they will be challenged academically to expand their level of understanding. Our program will primarily focus on Science, Technology, Engineering, and Math (STEM) subjects. Our goal is to provide STEM exposure to your child, as we believe preparing students at a young age for a future in STEM is essential. It is important to note that there will be an influx of jobs within these fields over the next few decades. So, our purpose is to make sure your child and many others will be prepared for this wave of opportunity. There is no reason why your child should be left behind or out of these fields in the future.
        </p>

        <p>As an organization, we truly hope that we can establish a strong genuine relationship with you and your child to ensure their success in our program. We do realize that there is a lack of affordable tutoring facilities and technology centers within the City of Inglewood and surrounding areas. This severely limits opportunities for your child to develop life-long STEM practices and mastery of necessary skills. We aim to change that with the establishment of Great Minds STEM Society.
        </p>

        <p>Again, we look forward to working with you and your child. The future success of your child is a shared responsibility that must be constantly monitored.</p>

        <p>Sincerely, <br><br> Brian Everitt <br> Founder</p>

